<DocsLayout title="Job Costing" section="Auxiliary Modules">
  <h2>Overview</h2>
  <p>
    Track profitability using Job Costing in Field Promax. View and analyze costs
    related to technicians, work orders, and estimates to understand your business's
    financial performance.
  </p>
  <p>
    Unlike traditional methods where profit analysis happens at month-end, Field Promax
    enables you to analyze profits before submitting estimates or invoicing — empowering
    data-driven decisions early on.
  </p>

  <h2>How to Access</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Go to <strong>Settings</strong> → <strong>Manage Users</strong> → <strong>Manage Permissions</strong> to enable Job Costing access</li>
    <li>Access Job Costing Reports from the <strong>Reports</strong> section</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Job Costing in Work Orders</h2>
  <img src="/images/auxiliary-modules/auxillarymodules_jobcosting_01.webp" alt="Job Costing Work Order" />
  <ol>
    <li>Open the desired <strong>Work Order</strong></li>
    <li>Navigate to the <strong>Job Costing</strong> tab at the bottom</li>
    <li>View profitability including technician, material, and product costs</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Job Costing in Estimates</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Open the desired <strong>Estimate</strong></li>
    <li>Navigate to the <strong>Job Costing</strong> tab at the bottom</li>
    <li>View profitability analysis before sending for approval</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Job Costing Reports</h2>
  <img src="/images/auxiliary-modules/auxillarymodules_jobcosting_02.png" alt="Job Costing Reports" />
  <p>For a comprehensive view across multiple jobs:</p>
  <ol>
    <li>Go to the <strong>Reports</strong> section</li>
    <li>Under <strong>Job Costing</strong>, select the report you want to view</li>
    <li>Analyze profitability trends and identify areas for improvement</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Notifications & Permissions</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Only <strong>Administrators</strong> can grant Job Costing access to other users</li>
    <li>Configure who can view cost information based on roles</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Tips</h2>
  <div class="callout callout-tip">
    <p>
      <strong>Review job costing regularly</strong> to ensure accurate cost tracking and profitability.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Run reports</strong> to track profitability across different work orders and estimates.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Analyze before invoicing</strong> to catch any pricing adjustments needed.
    </p>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
